sequenceDiagram
    participant Controller as KServe Controller
    participant Storage as Model Storage<br/>(S3/GCS/Azure/PVC)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Server as autogluon-server<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>8081/TCP gRPC
    participant AutoGluon as AutoGluon Predictor<br/>(in-process)
    participant Client as Client / KServe Router
    participant Prom as Prometheus

    Note over Controller,Server: Flow 1: Pod Creation & Model Loading
    Controller->>Server: Create pod with autogluon-server image<br/>(InferenceService CR reconciliation)
    activate Server
    Server->>Server: runtime_paths.py: set writable CWD<br/>(/tmp, $HOME, or /home/kserve)
    Server->>Storage: kserve_storage.Storage.download()<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM / storage-config secret
    Storage-->>Server: Model artifacts (saved model directory)
    Server->>AutoGluon: predictor_detect.py: try TimeSeriesPredictor.load()
    alt Time Series Model
        AutoGluon-->>Server: TimeSeriesPredictor loaded
    else Tabular Model (fallback)
        Server->>AutoGluon: TabularPredictor.load()
        AutoGluon-->>Server: TabularPredictor loaded
    end
    Server->>Server: Register model in ModelRepository<br/>Start FastAPI (8080) + gRPC (8081)
    deactivate Server

    Note over Client,Server: Flow 2: v1 REST Inference (Tabular)
    Client->>Server: POST /v1/models/{name}:predict<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP, JSON payload<br/>{"instances": [[val1, val2, ...]]}
    activate Server
    Server->>Server: v1 protocol handler: parse JSON
    Server->>AutoGluon: TabularPredictor.predict(DataFrame)<br/>or predict_proba (if PREDICT_PROBA=true)
    AutoGluon-->>Server: Predictions array
    Server-->>Client: JSON response<br/>{"predictions": [...]}
    deactivate Server

    Note over Client,Server: Flow 3: v2 REST Inference (Tabular)
    Client->>Server: POST /v2/models/{name}/infer<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP, tensor payload<br/>{inputs: [{name, shape, datatype, data}]}
    activate Server
    Server->>Server: v2 protocol handler: map tensors to DataFrame<br/>(feature name resolution, dtype mapping)
    Server->>AutoGluon: TabularPredictor.predict(DataFrame)
    AutoGluon-->>Server: Predictions
    Server->>Server: Map predictions to v2 tensor format<br/>(INT64, FP64, BYTES)
    Server-->>Client: InferResponse<br/>{outputs: [{name, shape, datatype, data}]}
    deactivate Server

    Note over Client,Server: Flow 4: v1 REST Inference (Time Series)
    Client->>Server: POST /v1/models/{name}:predict<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP, JSON payload<br/>{"instances": [...], "parameters": {"known_covariates": [...]}}
    activate Server
    Server->>Server: v1 protocol handler: parse history + covariates
    Server->>AutoGluon: TimeSeriesPredictor.predict(TimeSeriesDataFrame)
    AutoGluon-->>Server: Forecast results
    Server-->>Client: JSON response<br/>{"predictions": [...]}
    deactivate Server

    Note over Client,Server: Flow 5: gRPC Inference
    Client->>Server: ModelInferRequest<br/>gRPC/HTTP2 8081/TCP
    activate Server
    Server->>AutoGluon: Predict via appropriate predictor
    AutoGluon-->>Server: Predictions
    Server-->>Client: ModelInferResponse
    deactivate Server

    Note over Prom,Server: Flow 6: Metrics Scrape
    Prom->>Server: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP
    Server-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics<br/>(request_preprocess_seconds,<br/>request_predict_seconds,<br/>request_postprocess_seconds,<br/>request_explain_seconds)
